A large 2 handed battle axe originating from the Ottoman Empire, Persia, India and surrounding countries and cultures. 

As a loanword taken through [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iranian_languages "Iranian languages") [Scythian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scythian_languages "Scythian languages"), the word _tabar_ is also used in most [Slavic languages](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slavic_languages "Slavic languages") as the word for axe (e.g. [Russian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_language "Russian language"): топор).

